TITLE: Making a Target Delivery API Request with cURL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to make a basic Target Delivery API request using cURL. It includes setting the client code, session ID, and providing context and execution parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adobe/target-nodejs-sdk/blob/main/openapi/delivery/markdown/api-description.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X POST \
  'https://`clientCode`.tt.omtrdc.net/rest/v1/delivery?client=`clientCode`&sessionId=d359234570e04f14e1faeeba02d6ab9914e' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'cache-control: no-cache' \
  -d '{
      "context": {
        "channel": "web",
        "browser" : {
          "host" : "demo"
        },
        "address" : {
          "url" : "http://demo.dev.tt-demo.com/demo/store/index.html"
        },
        "screen" : {
          "width" : 1200,
          "height": 1400
        }
      },
        "execute": {
        "mboxes" : [
          {
            "name" : "homepage",
            "index" : 1
          }
        ]
      }
    }'
```

